<br>
A level 20 melee wearing no haste does X damage.<br>
A level 20 melee wearing FBSS at 22% haste does X + 22% damage.<br>
A level 20 melee wearing CoF at 36% does X + 22% damage.<br>
<br>
Why? Because there is a maximum haste cap that raises with levels. Someone under level 60 cannot achieve 100% haste, even if they have spells and equipment that would give a level 60 100% haste. So even though the level 20 above with the CoF has a haste *potential* of X + 36%, he cannot get the full haste because it is capped lower.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
WHO CARES ABOUT HASTE CAPS AT LEVEL 20? For god's sake, since you have enough brain cells to type, try using a few of them to think for a change, or check out <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.dictionary.com/search?q=non+sequitur&r=3">www.dictionary.com/search...quitur&r=3</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> There is no focus cap that anybody has reported. A spell cast by a level 1 is focused by the same amount as the same spell cast by a level 60. <br>
<br>
The correct analogy here is to haste items that only work on certain quality of weapons. For example, FBSS would only work on 1h weapons with MN/del of 1.0 or worse (yak quality). RBG would only work on 1.7 or worse (lam quality), etc. Once a melee has acquired an FBSS, he has a minimum 22% damage increase FOREVER, regardless of how his character progresses or the quality of weapon used. When a caster gets a focus II item, he gets a TEMPORARY damage/efficiency increase that goes way down or disappears altogether as his character progresses. Why is it so hard to understand the difference?<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  And if you are still convinced this is some sort of Uber-cism against you, with The Man (VI) holding you down, remember anyone can access many of these same abilities if a mage is around, or through AA abilities which are NOT restricted to uber players only.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
1) I don't play this game in the normal sense, haven't in about a year and a half, and never will again. That makes it slightly difficult to be &quot;held down&quot;.<br>
<br>
2) I'm impressed. No, really. If you want to talk smack, where were you when I was playing? By my fuzzy recollection, I remember doing 14 server first ubers, and 7 of those were game-wide 1-4ths. How many have you done? And where's your title from top 4 on Test in the BotB? Who's the gimp again?<br>
<br>
3) If you'd actually bothered to read and understand my post, you'd see that I said that uber loot should have a higher focus percentage than anything else. It doesn't seem like rocket science to me that the focus percentage you get should scale based on the quality of loot you have, but evidently that's well beyond your grasp. If VI doesn't want lvl 1 players to have high focus percentages, they already have the mechanism in place.. recommended level.<br>
<br>
VI's intent was to balance casters and melee at high level, but these changes only balance &quot;uber&quot; players. Casters get minimal, if any, benefit from Focus II items, and Focus III is generally inaccessible. That's not balance. Now, before one of you even thinks it, I am NOT suggesting that a casual level 60 caster should be balanced with an uber melee. Having 30% or 35% focus items attainable like RBG and CoF are attainable (and lower percentage items as common as FBSS)would balance the casual casters. Keeping the 40% focus items on ubermobs would balance uber casters with uber melee and still keep the best loot on the ubermobs, as it should be. (again, percentages are for comparison only, and probably need to be reduced by 25-50%)<br>
<br>
To those of you saying that casters got something and should shut up and be happy with it, EA great big D. The implementation is logically flawed and doesn't address the problems it was meant to address. When did pointing out obvious flaws and suggesting simple improvements/alternatives become a bad thing?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#E9D756>- </font><a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr>Erollisi Marr, The Queen of Love</a><font color=#E9D756> - </font><a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes>Rants and Flames</a> <font color=#E9D756> - </font> <br>
